Title: Entity Framework Tutorial with ASP.NET MVC
Description: Entity Framework (EF) is an object-relational mapper that enables .NET developers to work with relational data using domain-specific objects. It eliminates the need for most of the data-access code that developers usually need to write.

Title: What is Entity Framework
Description: Entity Framework is an ORM framework. ORM stands for Object Relational Mapping.

Title: Entity Framework 6 Tutorial: Learn Entity Framework 6 from Scratch
Description: Entity Framework 6 Tutorial: learn how to store and query data using Entity Framework 6.

Title: Entity Framework Core 2.0: data, mobile, server, IoT, and more
Description: Entity Framework (EF) Core is a lightweight, extensible, and cross-platform version of the popular Entity Framework data access technology. In this demo-filled session we look at what's new in EF Core and what the team has planned for upcoming releases.

Title: Learning Entity Framework 6.1.3
Description: Get started with Entity Framework 6.1.3, including unit testing, CRUD operations, and code first from an existing database.

Title: Learning Entity Framework Core
Description: Learn how to improve code against existing databases (including less than desirable legacy databases) using Entity Framework Core.

Title: Accessing Existing Databases with Entity Framework Core
Description: Learn how to improve code against existing databases (including less than desirable legacy databases) using Entity Framework Core.

Title: Building Applications with Angular, ASP.NET Core, and Entity Framework Core
Description: Learn how to choose an application architecture to use with Entity Framework Core for several different scenarios.

Title: Practical Application Architecture with Entity Framework Core
Description: Learn how to choose an application architecture to use with Entity Framework Core for several different scenarios.
